   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON THIRTY-ONE THE FRINGES, THE WATER FOR IMPURITY,</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>AND THE CITIES OF REFUGE OUTLINE The fringes: The fringes indicating beauty.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>A cord of blue signifying a heavenly binding.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The water for impurity: Its composition: A red heifer.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Cedar wood, hyssop, and scarlet.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The living water for purification.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Its usage: To be sprinkled upon unclean persons.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To be sprinkled upon the tent in which a man dies and upon the open vessels and furnishings in it.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The cities of refuge: The number of the cities of refuge: A total of six cities.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Divided into two sets of three cities each.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The distribution of the cities.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The six cities being the same distance from each other.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The function of the cities.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The duration of stay in the cities of refuge.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The cities of refuge typifying Christ as our refuge.</S>
   </TEXT>
  </BODY>
